%F A010551 a(n) = floor(n/2)!*floor((n+1)/2)! is the number of permutations p of {1, 2, 3, ..., n} such that for every i, i and p(i) have the same parity, i.e., p(i) - i is even. - Avi Peretz (njk(AT)netvision.net.il), Feb 22 2001
%F A010551 a(n) = n!/binomial(n, floor(n/2)). - _Paul Barry_, Sep 12 2004
%F A010551 G.f.: Sum_{n>=0} x^n/a(n) = besseli(0, 2*x) + x*besseli(1, 2*x). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Apr 07 2005
%F A010551 E.g.f.: 1/(1-x/2) + (1/2)/(1-x/2)*arccos(1-x^2/2)/sqrt(1-x^2/4). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 28 2005
%F A010551 G.f.: G(0) where G(k) = 1 + (k+1)*x/(1 - x*(k+1)/(x*(k+1) + 1/G(k+1) )); (continued fraction, 3-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Nov 28 2012
%F A010551 D-finite with recurrence: 4*a(n) - 2*a(n-1) - n*(n-1)*a(n-2) = 0. - _R. J. Mathar_, Dec 03 2012
%F A010551 a(n) = a(n-1) * (a(n-2) + a(n-3)) / a(n-3) for all n >= 3. - _Michael Somos_, Dec 29 2012
%F A010551 G.f.: 1 + x + x^2*(1 + x*(G(0) - 1)/(x-1)) where G(k) = 1 - (k+2)/(1-x/(x - 1/(1 - (k+2)/(1-x/(x - 1/G(k+1) ))))); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Jan 15 2013
%F A010551 G.f.: 1 + x*(G(0) - 1)/(x-1) where G(k) = 1 - (k+1)/(1-x/(x - 1/(1 - (k+1)/(1-x/(x - 1/G(k+1) ))))); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Jan 15 2013
%F A010551 G.f.: 1 + x*G(0), where G(k) = 1 + x*(k+1)/(1 - x*(k+2)/(x*(k+2) + 1/G(k+1) )); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Jul 08 2013
%F A010551 G.f.: Q(0), where Q(k) = 1 + x*(k+1)/(1 - x*(k+1)/(x*(k+1) + 1/Q(k+1) )); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Aug 08 2013
%F A010551 Sum_{n >= 1} 1/a(n) = A130820. - _Peter Bala_, Jul 02 2016
%F A010551 a(n) ~  sqrt(Pi*n) * n! / 2^(n + 1/2). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 02 2018
%F A010551 Sum_{n>=0} (-1)^n/a(n) = A229020. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 12 2021
